      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and cool the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{olive-oil}} of olive oil",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook the onion for 5 minutes. Add garlic, mushroom stalks, and thyme and cook for 3 minutes. Add the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{spinach}} of spinach",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and cook until wilted. Press out all liquid through a sieve. Return to the pan and cook until the pan is completely dry. Season with ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{sea-salt-flakes}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{black-pepper}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ". Transfer to a bowl. Fold in the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{puy-lentils}} of Puy lentils",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ", ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{chestnut-cooked}} of chestnuts",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{walnuts}} of toasted walnuts",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ". Taste and adjust seasoning. Cool completely, then refrigerate until cold and firm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wrap and chill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C (180°C fan). Sear the whole portobello mushrooms in a hot, dry pan for 2 minutes per side. On a lightly floured surface, roll out the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{puff-pastry}} of puff pastry",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " to a large rectangle. Brush with ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{dijon-mustard}} of Dijon mustard",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ". Arrange the portobello mushrooms in a row down the centre. Spoon the cold filling over and around the mushrooms and shape into a firm log. Fold the pastry over, seal the edges firmly, and place seam-side down on a lined baking tray. Score the top. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Glaze and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush the wellington with ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{oat-milk}} of oat milk",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ". Allow to dry for 5 minutes, then apply a second coat. Bake for 35-40 minutes until deep golden. Rest for 10 minutes before slicing with a serrated knife.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "rows": [
            {
              "fix": "Cook the mushrooms and spinach until completely dry before combining with the lentils. The pan should be fully dry; no pooling liquid.",
              "cause": "Excess moisture in the filling",
              "symptom": "Pastry base is soggy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drain lentils thoroughly and pat dry. Refrigerate the filled wellington for at least 30 minutes before baking.",
              "cause": "Lentils not drained well enough, or filling not chilled before baking",
              "symptom": "Filling is too loose to slice"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Use unsweetened oat milk. Apply two thin coats, allowing the first to dry between applications.",
              "cause": "One coat applied, or milk was sweetened",
              "symptom": "Oat milk glaze is patchy or pale"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Check the ingredients panel: dairy-free puff pastry lists vegetable fat or palm oil rather than butter. Most own-brand supermarket ready-rolled puff pastry is dairy-free.",
              "cause": "Bought butter-enriched puff pastry rather than vegetable-fat",
              "symptom": "Pastry is not vegan"
            }
          ]
        },
        "content": []
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The vegan wellington has become the default centrepiece for vegan guests at British Christmas and Sunday tables. Its success depends on using the same technique as a meat wellington: careful preparation, a dry filling, and the patience to chill before baking. Made well, it competes on equal terms with the vegetarian version and holds its own alongside a full roast. Serve with roast potatoes, a mushroom gravy, and seasonal green vegetables.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
